{
  "stem": "1765.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But when I went to shul, mostly it was with my grandfather, and not with my parents.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But for the holidays, we all went, and I sat with my mother upstairs, or behind the mechitza.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My grandfather-- the grandfather I refer to is my father's father, and his name was Shlomo Ben Shimon Rudomin.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Actually, his name was Shlomo Mordechai Ben Shimon Rudomin.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the reason I am stressing this is that my father had this wonderful, wonderful habit of writing things down.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when he died, I found, among his papers, a list of every Yahrtzeit, of everyone that he knew who died natural deaths before the war.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's how I knew that my grandfather was not just Shlomo-- Solomon-- but Shlomo Mordechai Ben Shimon.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when I went to look up genealogical records in Salt Lake City, in the Mormon genealogical library-- which has very little material on Vilna and on Poland, but I found a listing for Shimon Rudomin in a list of men from Vilna who gave money for Eretz Israel in 1891.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I found it in 1991.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I go to shul on Weston Avenue in the 100th Street to Anche Chesed, my synagogue-- A-N-C-H-E, Chesed C-H-E-S-E-D-- very often I pick up a book which says given in memory of Shlomo Mordechai Ben Shimon Rudomin.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it's really nice.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if my father hadn't written it all down very carefully, I might not have known.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I wouldn't have known.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before the war?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, dear.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father was fun-loving.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Before the war, during the war, after the war, into his 90th year, everything was wonderful, wonderful.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And everything was splendid when-- when I was a little girl.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my mother was a serious person, very serious.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
